The paper deals with defending against adversarial attacks on deep neural networks (DNNs) used for image classification, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of an adaptive JPEG encoder to produce compressed images that are robust to these attacks, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques to defend against attacks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
